&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;As I was looking for a static site generator which supports &lt;code&gt;Markdown&lt;/code&gt; as an input, I came across &lt;a class="link" href="https://gohugo.io/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
&gt;Hugo&lt;/a&gt;. Hugo is an open source static site generator written in &lt;code&gt;Go&lt;/code&gt;. Hugo supports a lot of built in &lt;a class="link" href="https://themes.gohugo.io/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
&gt;Themes&lt;/a&gt;. One easy Theme to get started is the &lt;a class="link" href="https://github.com/CaiJimmy/hugo-theme-stack-starter" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
&gt;Hugo Theme Stack&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;a class="link" href="https://github.com/CaiJimmy" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
&gt;CaiJimmy&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>